data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` code won't compile. Replace with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

All expression-tree machinery is eliminated — `SetPropertyCalls` now uses `Action<>` instead of `Expression<Func<>>`.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names are uniquified.** Your `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` will get disambiguated column names (e.g. `Street` → `Street1`). Pin them explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types use full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was mapped to `BillingAddress_City` but is now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. Pin it to preserve the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
});
```

Without `HasColumnName()`, EF will generate a migration renaming the columns.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods like `CommandReaderExecuting` now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter (redacted SQL)
    {
        // Use logCommandText for safe logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Add the parameter to every method in the interface implementation.
